The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                               Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, April 28: The Serious Fraud Investigation Office (SFIO) has proposed a detailed investigation into Bank of Barodas involvement in the Satyam accounting fraud. According to a report by the SFIO to the ministry of corporate affairs, BoBs New York branch was being used by the IT firm to show non-existing current account balance.                             
	 New Delhi, April 28: The RBI has extended the concessional interest rate scheme to exporters by six months till October this year. The interest rate ceiling on pre-shipment rupee export credit and post-shipment credit was to expire on April 30.                             
	 Mumbai, April 28: The SBI has lowered interest rates on student loans to be sanctioned between May and September 2009. Interest rates for loans up to Rs 4 lakh will be reduced to 11.5 per cent from 11.75 per cent.                             
	 Mumbai, April 28: The RBI today allowed Indian firms to buy back foreign currency convertible bonds up to $100 million and extended the liberalised norms for raising debts from overseas till December 2009.                                                                                                                           
